social_posts.post_text: @danleykate , a USA Today Bestselling Author and Award Winning Playwright, has written a completely new work of theater. Danley has created a moving and emotionally charged one-act play. Late Shift, told in real-time, explores the ruts that individuals fall into, the insignificant day-to-day details that grow in significance with time, and the tragedy of people's unfulfilled goals while they wait for "The Moment." Bonnie has been a waitress on the late shift at Don's Diner for the past three decades. It is like a second home to her, and it gives her a sense of pride. Joe is running behind schedule on his first day on the job as a cook. As these two imperfect strangers meet while waiting for a 2:00 a.m. rush that may never materialize, they realize that goals and dreams arrive too late for some and that sometimes people are too late in their life to make a difference. Encore Theatre and Gallery presents a stunning two-hander with a unique world premiere, experiencing "Late Shift" in the form of Dinner Theatre on location at the famed @michaelsparkside. An upscale steak and seafood restaurant with a rooftop bar in Birmingham's Parkside neighborhood. Encore Theatre collaborates with the acclaimed modern venue to provide "Late Shift" as an interactive theatre experience for one evening and two showings only. The restaurant's chef will create a unique menu for the occasion, and each show will be preceded by a cocktail hour. February 25, 2023- We are delighted to announce that we’re back again with Karaoke Night! Come spend the evening with us as we raise funds while having fun. Mark your calendars and get ready to join in the event where we will gather funds to support The Encore’s mission. We continue to offer current, cutting-edge, and creative works in Birmingham, while also unapologetically presenting African-American works and showcasing minority talent. Mark this day on your calendars and make plans to either perform or or just come be in the midst of a Karaoke Party. The cost of admission is merely $10. Are you unable to attend? Not to worry; there is also the option to contribute via the ticket link. We appreciate everything you’ve done! The Encore Theatre and Gallery would like to thank you for your support.

April 6-8, 2023 - The new urban stage play "Ladies Night" is written and directed by Marc Raby, with musical direction by celebrated producer Dee Hill. Adult Subject Matter | Strong Language Lena may have taken her girlfriends' advice out of desperation or because she wasn't thinking clearly. Who takes advice like, "The best way to get over one man is to get under another" seriously? Lena, for whatever reason, does. As a consequence of that same advice, she now finds herself in the middle of an evening full of twists, turns, and drama. The type of drama that can only be stirred somewhere between the stilettos, peach mimosas  and the sounds of "Ladies Night". It's a nonstop roller coaster ride of relationship drama, shady business dealings, scandalous secrets, and so much more, all intertwined with a sexy sultry live soundtrack filled with love, emotion, and grit. Ladies Night is a new urban stage play that promises to be worthwhile entertainment. A stage play infused with R&B and Soul.  Not intended for audiences under 18. Get ready for the all new debut of our my new urban production, “Ladies Night: The Stage Play” coming to @encorebham April 6-8, 2023. At Encore Theatre and Gallery — It’s Opening Night! For the past few weeks, I have had the privilege of directing an extraordinary cast in the production of 12 Angry Jurors. It has been an absolute joy to witness the incredible talent and camaraderie that this diverse group of performers has brought to the stage. Their love, support, and mutual respect for one another have been truly inspiring.

As a director, each show is a unique and special journey, and this production of 12 Angry Jurors has been one that will forever hold a place in my heart. The dedication and hard work put in by every member of the cast and crew have allowed this play to come alive in ways we could have only imagined.

But that's not all! Tonight marks the start of our 5th year of shows at Encore Theatre and Gallery, and I couldn't be more excited. It is a testament to the enduring passion and loyalty of our audience that we are still here, ready to bring you another season of exceptional performances.

So, if you have a free evening, I urge you to come and join us. Get your tickets and experience this classi show. I promise you won't be disappointed. Its gripping drama and unforgettable characters.

Thank you for your continued support and belief in the power of live theater. We look forward to sharing this wonderful journey with you and creating lasting memories together.

See you at the show!

12 Angry Jurors opens August 30-Sept 2!!! Tickets are available at

And just like that, 12 Angry Jurors has made its debut at Encore Theatre and Gallery! What a fantastic evening it was, and we are incredibly grateful to all of you who joined us to support this exceptional cast. This marks the beginning of our 5th year at Encore Theatre and Gallery, and we couldn't have asked for a better start.

To those who haven't had the chance to see the show yet, no worries! There is still time to catch it tonight and tomorrow. Trust us, you don't want to miss out on this gripping production.

A special thank you goes out to all our amazing friends and patrons who took the time to join us. Your presence truly made the night even more memorable. Thank you to the amazing Erika Patrice Kellom for the amazing support in last as well my big cousin Harry W Turner Jr. and AudreyPooh Pope. Thank you Andrew Duxbury for the “icing on the cake” lol it was definitely a big hit. To each and everyone of you. We appreciate your continued support and couldn't have done it without you. 

Once again, thank you all so much for a beautiful night. We are thrilled to share this journey with all of you, and we look forward to many more incredible performances at Encore Theatre and Gallery.

Back in the director seat! LETS GO! November 10-19, 2023 | Birmingham, AL, Chicken & Biscuits is a raucous family comedy so full of laughter and love, it’ll leave you begging for seconds. The Jenkins family is coming together to celebrate the life of the family patriarch—hopefully without killing each other! But any hopes for a peaceful reunion unravel when a family secret shows up at the funeral. A feel-good comedy that will feed your soul. PG-13 COMEDY ~ Chicken & Biscuits contains adult language [Profanity] /situations and references

“…a brilliant script that’s fresh, relatable and laugh-out-loud funny…CHICKEN & BISCUITS is more than just a church service…it is a much-needed therapy session, a portrait of Black joy, love and laughter…This play is both a Hallelujah and an A-men.” —Variety.

“CHICKEN & BISCUITS serves up roaring comedy…The play provides audiences with the blessed release of almost continual laughter…” —Broadway News.

Can rivaling sisters Baneatta and Beverly bury their father without killing each other? This proves difficult when Beverly shows up to the chapel with her “blessings” on display. Meanwhile, Baneatta’s son brings his neurotic Jewish boyfriend along, knowing Baneatta disapproves, and Beverly’s nosy daughter keeps asking questions no one wants to answer. Baneatta’s pastor husband tries to mediate the family drama, but when a shocking family secret reveals itself at the pulpit, the two sisters are faced with a truth that could either heal or break them.

1 hour 45 Minutes (including a 15 minute intermission).

Marc Raby’s Soul Food: ‘Tis The Season, Again!

The hilarious holiday dramedy returns by popular demand! New Music, New Characters and whole new Soundtrack! Families have issues, or at least this one does! The estranged Mitchell family is hilarious, opinionated, and headstrong. Perfect timing, or perhaps forced timing, has finally reunited them all. Friendships can have flaws. Love lives can fade at times. But what about blood? Isn’t blood thicker than all of that? The Mitchell children are returning home for the holidays and they’re bringing all the drama and conflict that comes along with the dysfunctional holiday gatherings. Are the riffs caused by the secrets they keep? It’s time to find out. Marc Raby’s “Soul Food: Tis The Season, Again!” contains a dash of betrayal, a heaping of humor, and much more than a dab of drama. Get Your tickets today!

November 10-19, 2023 | Birmingham, AL, Chicken & Biscuits is a raucous family comedy so full of laughter and love, it’ll leave you begging for seconds. The Jenkins family is coming together to celebrate the life of the family patriarch—hopefully without killing each other! But any hopes for a peaceful reunion unravel when a family secret shows up at the funeral. A feel-good comedy that will feed your soul. PG-13 COMEDY ~ Chicken & Biscuits contains adult language [Profanity] /situations and references

“…a brilliant script that’s fresh, relatable and laugh-out-loud funny…CHICKEN & BISCUITS is more than just a church service…it is a much-needed therapy session, a portrait of Black joy, love and laughter…This play is both a Hallelujah and an A-men.” —Variety.

“CHICKEN & BISCUITS serves up roaring comedy…The play provides audiences with the blessed release of almost continual laughter…” —Broadway News.

Can rivaling sisters Baneatta and Beverly bury their father without killing each other? This proves difficult when Beverly shows up to the chapel with her “blessings” on display. Meanwhile, Baneatta’s son brings his neurotic Jewish boyfriend along, knowing Baneatta disapproves, and Beverly’s nosy daughter keeps asking questions no one wants to answer. Baneatta’s pastor husband tries to mediate the family drama, but when a shocking family secret reveals itself at the pulpit, the two sisters are faced with a truth that could either heal or break them.

1 hour 45 Minutes (including a 15 minute intermission).

CHICKEN AND BISCUITS Is presented by special arrangement with Broadway
Licensing, LLG, servicing the Dramatists Play Service collection.

This Giving Tuesday We would be honored to have your support for a worthy cause. I am raising funds for Encore Theatre and Gallery, and any contribution, whether it's $5 or $500, will make a difference. Thank you for your help. Below is information about the Encore Theatre and Gallery.

The Encore is a dream turned into reality, continuing Birmingham's legacy of producing amazing artists, particularly in the African-American community. We are a non-equity performance space dedicated to preserving African American theatrical staples and presenting plays by diverse voices for a diverse audience.

Our venue includes a main stage, an art gallery, and a studio stage/flex black box room. We are committed to filling a gap in the industry by telling the stories of marginalized people and providing a platform for established and emerging artists.

The Encore joins other African-American theater companies in producing works by minorities and highlighting their abilities. We believe that theater has the unique power to stimulate and heal the human spirit, and we invite you to dream with us and support our cause.

Your charitable contributions are crucial in creating relevant, representative theater and supporting our community service activities in the Magic City.
